  "prompt": "What does Hillary Clinton think of high-skill immigration?",
  "response": "Hillary Clinton has generally expressed support for high-skill immigration, viewing it as beneficial for the U.S. economy and innovation. During her political career, particularly in her 2016 presidential campaign, she advocated for policies that would attract and retain highly skilled workers, particularly in sectors like technology and engineering. Clinton argued that high-skill immigrants contribute significantly to the economy, help fill critical skill gaps, and drive growth. She also emphasized the importance of comprehensive immigration reform that balances the needs of the economy with fair treatment for all immigrants. For the most up-to-date information on her views, you might want to check her recent statements or interviews.",
